<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19617456058B8FD2FFB96FC98" author="Barkalov, A. V. &amp; Mutin, V. A." box="[760,1055,756,783]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" pagination="466 - 510" refId="ref10422" refString="Barkalov, A. V., Mutin, V. A. 2018. Checklist of the hover-flies (Diptera, Syrphidae) of Russia. Euroasian Entomological Journal, 17 (6), 466 - 510." type="journal article" year="2018">Barkalov &amp; Mutin, 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D1961745605E6DFD2FFF60FCB8" author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. &amp; Vanappelghem, C. &amp; Sarthou, V." pageId="7" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref12862" refString="Speight, M. C. D., Sarthou, J. - P., Vanappelghem, C., Sarthou, V. 2018. Maps of the departmental distribution of syrphid species in France (Diptera: Syrphidae). Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 100, 1 - 80. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin." type="journal article" year="2018">Speight et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D1961745605AB4FCCFFE1DFCB8" author="Speight, M. C. D." box="[244,404,788,815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 314" refId="ref12637" refString="Speight, M. C. D. 2020. Species accounts of European Syrphidae, 2020. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 104, 1 - 314. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin." type="journal article" year="2020">Speight, 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D1961745605BDEFCCFFDCDFCB8" author="Wakkie, B." box="[414,580,788,815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" refId="ref13847" refString="Wakkie, B. 2020. The world of Syrphidae website. Available from: http: // www. syrphidae. com / checklist _ overview. php (Accessed: April 27, 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Wakkie, 2020</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="32B014B0961745605816FCCFFD3FFCB9" box="[598,694,788,814]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605888FCCFFCD9FCB8" bold="true" box="[712,848,788,815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">first record</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A1854209617456F5AA3FCEFFCF9FE3E" blockId="7.[174,1233,628,1045]" lastBlockId="8.[166,1225,175,522]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="245" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">
Diagnosis. This species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39617456058CCFCEFFCD7FCD9" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[652,862,820,846]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="78D388329617456058CCFCEFFCD7FCD9" box="[652,862,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Cheilosia proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19617456059F8FCEFFBF7FCD8" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. &amp; Trifunov, S. &amp; Nikolic, T." box="[952,1150,820,847]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" pagination="33 - 50" refId="ref13789" refString="Vujic, A., Radenkovic, S., Trifunov, S., Nikolic, T. 2013. Key for European species of the Cheilosia proxima group (Diptera, Syrphidae) with a description of a new species. ZooKeys, 269, 33 - 50. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 269.4619" type="journal article" year="2013">Vujić et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605B24FC8FFD37FCF8" authority="Vujic, 1994" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[356,702,852,879]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605B24FC8FFDBAFCF9" box="[356,563,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Cheilosia balkana</emphasis>
Vujić, 
<quantity id="8D5FF9C59617456058C6FC8EFD37FCF8" box="[646,702,853,879]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06476" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" unit="in" value="1994.0">1994</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having first flagellomere black to blackishbrown, margin of upper calypter with short pale pile, frons not swollen, abdomen (including pregenital segments) covered in pale macrotrichia (
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D1961745605907FC4EFB93FC38" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[839,1050,917,943]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref13696" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S., Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al., 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605E26FC4EFEA6FC59" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pascuorum">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605E26FC4EFEA6FC59" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Cheilosia pascuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605B74FC6EFEE6FC58" bold="true" box="[308,367,949,975]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">male</emphasis>
can be separated from the male of 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605940FC6EFCF4FC58" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[768,893,949,975]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605940FC6EFCF4FC58" box="[768,893,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">C. balkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: tergite 3 dull medially (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605AEEFC0EFEA4FC78" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[174,301,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605AEEFC0EFEA4FC78" box="[174,301,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">C. balkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergite 3 shiny); vein M 
<subScript id="D623566596174560580EFC3CFDDFFC62" attach="left" box="[590,598,999,1013]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">1</subScript>
meeting vein R 
<subScript id="D6235665961745605950FC3CFCA3FC62" attach="left" box="[784,810,999,1013]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">4+5</subScript>
at right or obtuse angle (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961745605E13FC0FFB16FC78" box="[1107,1183,980,1007]" captionStart="Figs 26–29" captionStartId="7.[174,213,1797,1819]" captionTargetBox="[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-394@7.[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 26–29. Cheilosia pascuorum male: 26 — habitus, dorsal view; 27 — habitus, lateral view; 28 — head, frontal view; 29 —head, anterolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">fig. 26</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605AEEFC2EFEA5FB99" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[174,300,1012,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605AEEFC2EFEA5FB99" box="[174,300,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">C. balkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, vein M 
<subScript id="D6235665961745605BCBFBDCFE1AFB82" attach="left" box="[395,403,1031,1045]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">1</subScript>
meeting vein R 
<subScript id="D6235665961745605809FBDCFDEDFB82" attach="left" box="[585,612,1031,1045]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">4+5</subScript>
at an acute angle); arista bare (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A596174560598AFC2FFB9CFB98" box="[970,1045,1012,1039]" captionStart="Figs 26–29" captionStartId="7.[174,213,1797,1819]" captionTargetBox="[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-394@7.[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 26–29. Cheilosia pascuorum male: 26 — habitus, dorsal view; 27 — habitus, lateral view; 28 — head, frontal view; 29 —head, anterolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">fig. 29</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605E0CFC2EFB40FB99" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[1100,1225,1012,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605E0CFC2EFB40FB99" box="[1100,1225,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">C. balkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, arista with short microtrichia); dorsal lobe of gonostylus very broad basally (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5E04FF6BFB4BFF5E" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="1994" box="[1092,1218,175,202]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balkana">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5E04FF6BFB4BFF5E" box="[1092,1218,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. balkana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal lobe of gonostylus basally narrowed) (
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19618456F58FEFF14FC06FF7E" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[702,911,207,234]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref13696" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S., Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al., 2001</bibRefCitation>
). From the similar species 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5AE6FF2BFD9BFE9E" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[166,530,239,266]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5AE6FF2BFEA2FE9E" box="[166,299,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. proxima</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5811FF2BFC37FE9E" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1838)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[593,958,239,266]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5811FF2BFD5EFE9E" box="[593,727,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. gigantea</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1838)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F598DFF2BFBF8FE9E" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[973,1137,240,266]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pascuorum">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F598DFF2BFBF8FE9E" box="[973,1137,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. pascuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by: abdomen entirely with pale macrotrichia (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A59618456F5906FED4FC4DFEBE" box="[838,964,271,297]" captionStart="Figs 26–29" captionStartId="7.[174,213,1797,1819]" captionTargetBox="[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-394@7.[205,1201,1098,1770]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 26–29. Cheilosia pascuorum male: 26 — habitus, dorsal view; 27 — habitus, lateral view; 28 — head, frontal view; 29 —head, anterolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455538/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">figs 26, 27</figureCitation>
) (in others, abdomen partly with black macrotrichia, at least pregenital segments with a few black macrotrichia). Additionally, from 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5BCBFE8BFD86FEFE" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[395,527,336,362]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5BCBFE8BFD86FEFE" box="[395,527,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by its larger size, usually not smaller than 
<quantity id="8D5FF9C59618456F5E35FE94FB40FEFD" box="[1141,1225,335,362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
(
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5AF0FEABFEBFFE1E" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[176,310,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5AF0FEABFEBFFE1E" box="[176,310,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller, usually 
<quantity id="8D5FF9C59618456F5863FEB4FD05FE1D" box="[547,652,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9 mm</quantity>
). Genitalia of these species are different by the shape of the dorsal lobe of the gonostylus (
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19618456F58D9FE54FCEAFE3E" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[665,867,399,426]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref13696" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S., Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al., 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1ED804A8961745605AEEF8DEFD8AF8A1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455538" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6455538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" startId="7.[174,213,1797,1819]" targetBox="[205,1201,1098,1770]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="4A185420961745605AEEF8DEFD8AF8A1" blockId="7.[174,1232,1797,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">
Figs 26–29. 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961745605B5FF8DEFE6DF88C" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[287,484,1797,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pascuorum">
<emphasis id="78D38832961745605B5FF8DEFE6DF88C" box="[287,484,1797,1819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Cheilosia pascuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male: 26 — habitus, dorsal view; 27 — habitus, lateral view; 28 — head, frontal view; 29 —head, anterolateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4A1854209618456F5A9BFE74FEB1FE7E" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">
The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA39618456F5BD6FE6BFDBEFE5E" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[406,567,432,458]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pascuorum">
<emphasis id="78D388329618456F5BD6FE6BFDBEFE5E" box="[406,567,432,458]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">C. pascuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been prepared and compared with figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19618456F5EC8FE74FEBDFE7E" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." pageId="8" pageNumber="245" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref13696" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S., Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A1854209618456F5A9BFE2BFB4DFD9E" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,522]" box="[219,1220,495,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">
Note. This species is regarded as generally endangered in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="2E3629D19618456F59ADFE34FB3EFD9E" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[1005,1207,495,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref13696" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S., Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al., 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
